      "side": 1,
      "message": "minor: I think this whole piece of code doesn\u0027t even need to mention ldiskfs: you can simply first iterate over the inode_xattrs to get the trusted.lov assign the lum to it, then if lum is null, use the `get_lov_user_md` function, like so:\n```\nfor (int i...)\n    if (_inode_xattrs[i].key[0] \u003d\u003d \u0027t\u0027 \u0026\u0026\n        !strcmp(_inode_xattrs[i].key, \"trusted.lov\"))\n        lum \u003d ...\n        break\n\nif (!lum)\n    lum \u003d get_lov_user_md(fd)\n```\n\nIt\u0027s pretty much guaranteed that an entry in a Lustre FS has the trusted.lov attribute set, to let\u0027s just always use it instead of always doing an ioctl",
